Calling Peaks on IKZF1 ChIP data in activated CD4+ T cells

In this vistory, I describe the steps used to call peaks on my IKZF1 ChIP data. This vistory closely follows that of the publically available ChIP-Seq vistory on vistory DB (https://www.bioinformatics.babraham.ac.uk/vistorydb/)

I begin by inputting the mapped reads for the IKZF1 ChIP data and the input file into SeqMonk.

Creating a blacklist

I then create a blacklist of genomic regions which have unusual coverage in the input sample.

New Probe Set:All probes (6176584 probes)

Running windows of size 500 with step size 500

Probes Quantitated

Read Count Quantitation using All Reads correcting for total count to largest store

From the histogram, of quantitated value in the input we can see that there are some very highly covered outliers. I apply a filter (>50) to extract the badly behaving regions of the genome.

New Probe List: Good input (5222066 probes)

[Probe Values Filter] Filter on probes in All probes where exactly 1 of IKZF1.bam had a value between 1.0 and 50.0. Quantitation was Read Count Quantitation using All Reads correcting for total count to largest store

An example of regions which have been blacklisted is shown below. We can see that these contain lots of duplicate reads.

New Probe List: Bad input (57197 probes)

[Probe Values Filter] Filter on probes in All probes where exactly 1 of IKZF1.bam had a value above 50.0. Quantitation was Read Count Quantitation using All Reads correcting for total count to largest store

Annotation Sets Added

Added 1 annotation set Bad input - 57197 features

When looking genome wide, we see that these are evenly spread throughout the genome.

Define peaks

I use the MACS peak caller to call peaks, excluding those overlapping my black listed regions.

New Probe Set:MACS peaks (28158 probes)

MACS peaks using chip samples IKZF1.bam and input samples ChIPLib_input.bam. Fragment size was 300. Significance threshold was 1.0E-5

Probes Quantitated

Read Count Quantitation using All Reads correcting for total count to largest store

New Probe List: Not Overlapping Bad input (4909 probes)

[Feature Filter] Filter probes in MACS peaks on regions based on Bad input Over feature relationship is Not Overlapping

Finally, a create a report of these peaks not overlapping the black listed regions.
